The paper focuses on applying a new architecture of convolutional neural network (CNN) called bilinear CNN (B-CNN) to the challenging task of face recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses fine-tuning and pre-training techniques, which are common in machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and feature extraction, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of deep learning and neural networks could also suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the B-CNN model on a benchmark dataset, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
